      right: ["MoCA ≤25 with declining instrumental ADLs = probable MCI or dementia requiring further evaluation", "Acute confusion with fluctuating attention + recent medication change = delirium until proven otherwise", "Progressive memory loss + word-finding difficulty + getting lost in familiar places = Alzheimer's pattern", "Personality change + disinhibition + executive dysfunction with preserved memory = frontotemporal dementia pattern"]
